BoE’s Spencer Dale Warns of Global ‘Downward Spiral,’ Mail Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-09-29T06:23:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/boe-s-spencer-dale-warns-of-global-downward-spiral-mail-says.html
Bank of England Chief Economist
 Spencer Dale  said the world’s economy was at risk of a downward
spiral and U.K. inflation would jump to 5 percent before falling
sharply, the  Daily Mail  reported, citing an interview.  Dale said double-digit price increases by energy suppliers
was behind the inflation rise, although it would start to fall
“very sharply” next year, the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
